istic inspiration-has not only been a profound force in history, but may be fundamental to the human condition itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAlcoholic beveragesxHistory. 0aAlcoholic beveragesxSocial aspects. 0aDrinking of alcoholic beveragesxHistory. 0aDrinking of alcoholic beveragesxSocial aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh  aagrarian society.  aalcohol history.  aalcoholic beverages.  aanthropology.  aarchaeology.  acacao.  acoffee table book.  acorn beer.  acreation of alcohol.  aevolution.  afermented beverages.  afermenting.  afood and sociology.  afood and wine.  afood history.  agastronomy.  ahistory of alcohol.  ahuman condition.  aliquid courage.  amead.  amillet.  amodern world.  aprovocative hypothesis.  areligious symbol.  arice wine.  arole of alcohol in society.  asearch for booze.  asocial lubricant.  asorghum.  aspirits.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094468840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520944688423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520944688/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles